g.text: Button matrix for the GRBL controller.
Positive common, if a negative common is desired
then swap the GND and +5V and reverse the diodes.
Capacitors C201 - C207 are optional but recommended
for hardware debouncing. The code is configured
for software debouncing as well and can be used
instead of or along with the hardware debouncing.
The switches should be momentary. I used DPST
because that is what I had in hand. Otherwise
You can also buy a button matrix and connected directly
